d the silent cinema, and how that interaction appeared from the perspective of women at work across both realms. A wealth of archival research provides fresh insights into Dutch stage and screen comedy, the French revue, and the American Northwest drama of the 1910s, illuminating the lives of three important women in the early era of film.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aArts in general. 0aMotion picture actors and actressesvBiography. 0aMotion pictures. 0aSilent filmsxHistory and criticism. 0aWomen in motion pictures. 4aFilm Studies. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  aWomen's Careers, Silent Film, Popular Theatre, Acting, Filmmaking.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017z978311060644708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066293140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048524518zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048524518zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048524518.jpg  a978-3-11-060644-7 AUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066293-1 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-066731-8 AUP eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA